I’m still processing how amazing running the @NYCMarathon was. A 26.2 mile journey of self-discovery, resilience, mental toughness and triumph. Initially my intention was to run this marathon free of any time constraints. 48 hours before the race I had a talk with the boss man @Diddy where he shared his NYC marathon experience with me and told me if I didn’t finish in less than 4:30:00 or beat his marathon time of 4:14:53, not to bother calling him after the race. It was at that moment a challenge was issued and fire was lit….

I was fortunate to have my brother and Co-Captain of the @NoSleepingRunningClub @JRJensen12 alongside me for his first and my 3rd marathon. We locked in on our goal and together we tackled every mile, every hill and turned every obstacle into stepping stones toward the finish line. 

When you believe in yourself, there truly are no limits to what you’re capable of. My previous marathon time was 4:40:00. We crossed the finish line at 4:12:43 setting new personal bests for us both and beating @Diddy’s time by 2 minutes. 

Thank you to my family & all of my friends who I saw cheering on the sidelines and big love to everyone who saw me that I ran past because I was locked in. My heart is full, my legs are still sore and I think I’m about to lose a toenail. Until the next one! 👏🏽⚠️🫡
